which can be rearranged to become
:formula_26

As the &quot;log-evidence&quot; formula_27 is fixed with respect to formula_28, maximizing the final term formula_29 minimizes the KL divergence of formula_28 from formula_31. By appropriate choice of formula_28, formula_29 becomes tractable to compute and to maximize. Hence we have both an analytical approximation formula_28 for the posterior formula_6, and a lower bound formula_29 for the log-evidence formula_27 (since the KL-divergence is non-negative).

The lower bound formula_29 is known as the (negative) variational free energy in analogy with thermodynamic free energy because it can also be expressed as a negative energy formula_39 plus the entropy of formula_28. The term formula_29 is also known as Evidence Lower Bound, abbreviated as ELBO, to emphasize that it is a lower (worst-case) bound on the log-evidence of the data.

