===Factorized approximation===
Assume that formula_108, i.e. that the posterior distribution factorizes into independent factors for formula_93 and formula_94. This type of assumption underlies the variational Bayesian method. The true posterior distribution does not in fact factor this way (in fact, in this simple case, it is known to be a Gaussian-gamma distribution), and hence the result we obtain will be an approximation.

