* Mult() is a multinomial distribution over a single observation (equivalent to a categorical distribution). The state space is a &quot;one-of-K&quot; representation, i.e., a formula_159-dimensional vector in which one of the elements is 1 (specifying the identity of the observation) and all other elements are 0.
